verbose_text: The baseline assessment included medical history, physical examination, anthropometric status (body weight / height, BMI), blood pressure, electrocardiogram, laboratory diagnostics (complete blood count, coagulation, hepatic profile, renal profile, lipid profile, fasting blood glucose levels, glycosylated hemoglobin--HbA1c, and CRP) and transabdominal ultrasound, upper gastrointestinal endoscopy.
